# TypeScript conventions

## Style
- Functional components with hooks only, no class components
- Type all props with `interface`, not `type` (reserve `type` for unions and utilities)
- Tailwind utility classes, no separate CSS files
- Named exports, except for Next.js pages and layouts which require default

## No `any`
If you don't know the type, use `unknown` and narrow it. `any` is not permitted,
including in test files and including as `as any` to silence an error.

## Zod is the source of truth
Define the schema, infer the type from it. Never hand-write a type that duplicates
a schema.

```ts
// ✅
export const ResponseSchema = z.object({
  questionId: z.string(),
  value: z.union([z.boolean(), z.number(), z.string()]),
  source: z.enum(["child", "parent", "proxy"]),
  answeredAt: z.string().datetime(),
});
export type Response = z.infer<typeof ResponseSchema>;

// ❌ Type and schema drift apart within a week
interface Response { questionId: string; value: unknown; }
```

Validate at every trust boundary: API route input, LLM output, database reads,
FHIR construction.

## Single responsibility
Each function does one thing. If describing it needs the word "and", split it.

```ts
// ❌
function saveResponsesAndBuildSummaryAndWriteFhir(r: Response[]) { ... }

// ✅
function saveResponses(r: Response[]): Promise<void> { ... }
function buildSummary(r: Response[], s: Session): SessionSummary { ... }
function toQuestionnaireResponse(s: SessionSummary): QuestionnaireResponse { ... }
```

## DRY
Write the same logic twice, extract it. Shared logic between routes belongs in
`lib/`, not copy-pasted across route handlers.

## Component structure
- One component per file
- Over ~100 lines, extract sub-components
- No fetch calls inside components — use `lib/api.ts` or a hook in `hooks/`
- Child-facing instrument components take `value` and `onChange` and hold no
  session state of their own

## Questions are data, not code
The standard nine and the supplementary library are typed config in `lib/questions/`.
Adding a question means adding an entry there — never a new branch in a component.

```ts
export interface QuestionDef {
  id: string;
  modality: "yes_no" | "faces_scale" | "body_map" | "bristol" | "count" | "picture_choice";
  instrument: string | null;   // e.g. "FPS-R", "Rome IV"
  tier: ("5-8" | "9-12")[];
  i18nKey: string;
  respondent: "child" | "parent";
  schema: z.ZodTypeAny;
}
```

## Server boundary
Anything touching the Anthropic key, the database service role, or PHI runs in
`app/api/` or a server component. Mark client components `"use client"` explicitly
and keep them thin.
